# =============================================================================
# IMPORTANT NOTES
# =============================================================================

# 1. All custom environment variables must start with REACT_APP_
# 2. Environment variables are embedded at build time, not runtime
# 3. Never put sensitive data in React environment variables (they're public)
# 4. Restart development server after changing environment variables
# 5. Different .env files are loaded based on NODE_ENV and file priority:
#    - .env.production.local (production, local overrides)
#    - .env.local (always loaded except in test)
#    - .env.production (production)
#    - .env (default)

# 6. To use this template:
#    - Copy to .env.production in your frontend directory
#    - Update API URLs to match your backend deployment
#    - Configure feature flags as needed
#    - Remove development/staging overrides
#    - Test build: npm run build

